The bson_as_json function has a shortcut for an empty object, which has this code:

{code}
   if (bson_empty0 (bson)) {
      if (length) {
         *length = 2;
      }

      return bson_strdup ("{ }");
   }
{code}

https://github.com/mongodb/libbson/blob/master/src/bson/bson.c#L2672

As you can see, the returned string is three characters long, but we only return 2 as the output length. It should be 3.

It would be nice to have a helper to make it easier to remove a particular gridfs file. This should remove the gridfs file and any chunks associated with it.

Something like:

{code}
if (!mongoc_gridfs_file_remove (file, &error)) {
   fprintf (stderr, "%s\n", error.message);
}
mongoc_gridfs_destroy (file);
{code}

There is a bug in the C driver where it appends undefined instead of null in bson_append_iter (https://github.com/mongodb/libbson/blob/master/src/bson/bson.c#L1245-L1247):
{code:c}
case BSON_TYPE_NULL:
   ret = bson_append_undefined (bson, key, key_length);
   break;
{code}

A similar append in bson_append_value at https://github.com/mongodb/libbson/blob/master/src/bson/bson.c#L1723-L1725 seems to be correctly implemented.

{code:c}
if (!node.replSet || !!strcmp (node.replSet, replSet)) {
   MONGOC_INFO("%s: Got replicaSet \"%s\" expected \"%s\".",
               iter->host_and_port, node.replSet, replSet);
}
{code}

Error condition in the above listed code will cause a crash for node.replSet == null condition while trying tot print that value.

This is generally unsafe and should rather be something like {{ (node.replSet ? node.replSet : "<null>") }} in the MONGOC_INFO.
